# Festag — no mobile auth container scroll

On **mobile** (≤768px), auth entry and auth chrome containers must **never** be finger-scrollable.

## Surfaces

- `/enter` (Client / Developer chooser + video)
- `/login`, `/register` (`.al-root` / `.al-mobile-sheet` / `.al-sheet-body` / `.al-main`)
- Dev login / onboarding auth sheets that share the same mobile chrome

## Do

- Keep `overflow: hidden` on the mobile auth shell (no rubber-band / drag scroll)
- Keep auth root fixed to the viewport on mobile so iOS cannot leave the page scrolled blank after keyboard dismiss
- Use `interactiveWidget: 'overlays-content'` so the keyboard overlays instead of shrinking/clipping the layout (which made „Anmelden“ vanish into white)
- When a field is focused, shift the form by the **full overlap** under the keyboard (native-like) — then reset `--al-kb-shift` and `scrollTop` on blur
- Keep „Anmelden“ / hero visible; never let keyboard focus wipe the title

## Do not

- `overflow-y: auto` / `scroll` on `.al-main`, `.al-sheet-body`, `.al-mobile-sheet`, `.ae-root` for idle browsing
- `scrollIntoView` / large forced jumps that yank the email field to the top
- `interactiveWidget: 'resizes-content'` on auth — it collapses `100dvh` layouts and clips the hero
- Reintroduce finger-scroll “just for short phones” — shorten UI instead

When touching mobile auth layout, verify: no finger scroll, hero stays after focus/blur, keyboard sits under the focused field without overshooting.
